The paper focuses on the design and implementation of a solver for optimization problems over normalized databases, which suggests a strong connection to the database (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of aggregates and factorized computation also suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the title of the paper, "Ac Dc In Database Learning Thunderstruck," includes a reference to the band AC/DC, which could suggest a connection to distributed computing (cs.DC).
